| name = SMS
| "SMS" stands for "''[[Seiner Majestät Schiff]]''", or "His Majesty's Ship". ''Bayern'' is the German name for [[Bavaria]].
}}

{{efn
| name = bigger guns
| The 38&nbsp;cm gun fired a {{convert|750|kg|adj=on}} shell while the 30.5&nbsp;cm gun fired a {{convert|405|kg|abbr=on}} shell. ''Bayern'' had a [[broadside]] weight of {{convert|6000|kg|abbr=on}} with all eight guns while ''König''{{'}}s ten guns had a broadside weight of {{convert|4050|kg|abbr=on}}. See: {{harvnb|Gardiner & Gray|p=140}}.
}}

{{efn
| name = Parsons-Turbinia
